World Rally Champions,&nbsp;Sebastian Ogier, and Ott&nbsp;Tanak are ready to take on the challenge in the WRC Safari Rally.&nbsp;The two drivers jetted into the country ahead of the event where they&nbsp;will be hunting down wins in their first?ever Kenyan rallying experience. A total of 58 crews will participate in the rally&nbsp;set to&nbsp;run from 24th to 27th June.